    "is_new": true,
    "db_statements": ["a certain siyyid known as Siyyid-i-S̱his̱h-Parí, whose function was to carry the mace before the Imám-Jum‘ih, insolently shouted: 'Enough of this idle chatter!'"],
    "mention_idxs": [319]
  },
  {
    "canonical_name": "S̱hayḵh ‘Alí Mírzá",
    "entity_type": "person",
    "side": "Bábí",
    "is_new": true,
    "db_statements": ["Among them was S̱hayḵh ‘Alí Mírzá, the nephew of this same Imám-Jum‘ih, a young man who had just attained the age of maturity.", "in the year 1267 A.H. he was privileged to meet Bahá’u’lláh in ‘Iráq."],
    "mention_idxs": [321]
  },
  {
    "canonical_name": "Mírzá Raḥím-i-Ḵhabbáz",
    "entity_type": "person",
    "side": "Bábí",
    "is_new": true,
    "db_statements": ["Among them also was Mírzá Raḥím-i-Ḵhabbáz, who distinguished himself by his fearlessness and fiery ardour. He relaxed not in his efforts until the hour of his death."],
    "mention_idxs": [324]
  },
  {
    "canonical_name": "Ḥájí Muḥammad-Bisáṭ",
    "entity_type": "person",
    "side": "Bábí",
    "is_new": true,
    "db_statements": ["the late Ḥájí Muḥammad-Bisáṭ, a man well-versed in the metaphysical teachings of Islám and a great admirer of both S̱hayḵh Aḥmad and Siyyid Káẓim."],
    "mention_idxs": [326]
  },
  {
    "canonical_name": "Mírzá Hádí",
    "entity_type": "person",
    "side": "Bábí",
    "is_new": true,
    "db_statements": ["Mírzá Hádí, the brother of Mírzá Muḥammad-‘Alí, both residents of Iṣfahán, were among those companions whose vision of the glory and sublimity of the Faith the expressed misgivings of the evil whisperers had failed to obscure."],
    "mention_idxs": [328, 333, 334]
  },
  {
    "canonical_name": "Muḥammad-i-Ḥaná-Sáb",
    "entity_type": "person",
    "side": "Bábí",
    "is_new": true,
    "db_statements": ["a certain Muḥammad-i-Ḥaná-Sáb, also a resident of Iṣfahán, who is now serving in the home of Bahá’u’lláh."],
    "mention_idxs": [328]
  },
  {
    "canonical_name": "Mullá Javád-i-Barag̱hání",
    "entity_type": "person",
    "side": "",
    "is_new": true,
    "db_statements": ["Mullá Javád-i-Barag̱hání and Mullá ‘Abdu’l-‘Alíy-i-Harátí, both of whom feigned submission to the Revelation of the Báb in the hope of satisfying their ambition for leadership.", "'May Thy condemnation, O God!' He wrote, with reference to Mullá Javád and Mullá ‘Abdu’l-‘Alí, 'rest upon the Jibt and Ṭág̱hút, the twin idols of this perverse people.'"],
    "mention_idxs": [329, 330, 333, 344]
  },
  {
    "canonical_name": "Mullá ‘Abdu’l-‘Alíy-i-Harátí",
    "entity_type": "person",
    "side": "",
    "is_new": true,
    "db_statements": ["Mullá Javád-i-Barag̱hání and Mullá ‘Abdu’l-‘Alíy-i-Harátí, both of whom feigned submission to the Revelation of the Báb in the hope of satisfying their ambition for leadership. They both strove secretly to undermine the enviable position achieved by Mullá Ḥusayn."],
    "mention_idxs": [329, 333]
  },
  {
    "canonical_name": "Mírzá Ibráhím-i-S̱hírází",
    "entity_type": "person",
    "side": "",
    "is_new": true,
    "db_statements": ["The first group to reach the city and meet the Báb... consisted of Mírzá Muḥammad-‘Alíy-i-Nahrí, Mírzá Hádí, his brother; Mullá ‘Abdu’l-Karím-i-Qazvíní, Mullá Javád-i-Barag̱hání, Mullá ‘Abdu’l-‘Alíy-i-Harátí, and Mírzá Ibráhím-i-S̱hírází."],
    "mention_idxs": [333]
  },
  {
    "canonical_name": "Mullá ‘Abdu’l-Karím-i-Íravání",
    "entity_type": "person",
    "side": "",
    "is_new": true,
    "db_statements": ["I was a faithful attendant at the lectures given by Mullá ‘Abdu’l-Karím-i-Íravání, who, in those days, ranked as the most outstanding divine of Qazvín."],
    "mention_idxs": [335]
  },
  {
    "canonical_name": "Ḥájí Ḥusayn-‘Alí",
    "entity_type": "person",
    "side": "",
    "is_new": true,
    "db_statements": ["both my father and my elder uncle, Ḥájí Ḥusayn-‘Alí, both of whom were greatly esteemed throughout Qazvín, were preparing a feast in my honour."],
    "mention_idxs": [336]
  },
  {
    "canonical_name": "Ḥájí Alláh-Vardí",
    "entity_type": "person",
    "side": "",
    "is_new": true,
    "db_statements": ["I immediately decided to consult Ḥájí Alláh-Vardí, father of Muḥammad-Javád-i-Farhádí, a man known throughout Qazvín for his deep spiritual insight."],
    "mention_idxs": [338, 339]
  },
  {
    "canonical_name": "Muḥammad-Javád-i-Farhádí",
    "entity_type": "person",
    "side": "",
    "is_new": true,
    "db_statements": ["Ḥájí Alláh-Vardí, father of Muḥammad-Javád-i-Farhádí, a man known throughout Qazvín for his deep spiritual insight."],
    "mention_idxs": [338]
  },
  {
    "canonical_name": "‘Abdu’l-Ḥamíd-i-Qazvíní",
    "entity_type": "person",
    "side": "Bábí",
    "is_new": true,
    "db_statements": ["My brother, ‘Abdu’l-Ḥamíd [who later quaffed the cup of martyrdom in Ṭihrán], accompanied me on my journey to Karbilá."],
    "mention_idxs": [340]
  },
  {
    "canonical_name": "Mullá Muḥammad-i-Mu‘allim",
    "entity_type": "person",
    "side": "Bábí",
    "is_new": true,
    "db_statements": ["On my way I met, in Ṭihrán, Mullá Muḥammad-i-Mu‘allim, who acquainted me with the nature of this Call, and informed me that those who had acknowledged it had gathered in Karbilá."],
    "mention_idxs": [345]
  },
  {
    "canonical_name": "Mírzá Luṭf-‘Alí",
    "entity_type": "person",
    "side": "",
    "is_new": true,
    "db_statements": ["In those days Siyyid Yaḥyá was residing in Ṭihrán in the house of Mírzá Luṭf-‘Alí, the Master of Ceremonies to the S̱háh."],
    "mention_idxs": [350]
  },
  {
    "canonical_name": "Mullá Iskandar",
    "entity_type": "person",
    "side": "Bábí",
    "is_new": true,
    "db_statements": ["Ḥujjat deputed one of his disciples, Mullá Iskandar, in whom he reposed the fullest confidence, to enquire into the whole matter.", "Mullá Iskandar attained the presence of the Báb and felt immediately the regenerating power of His influence. He tarried forty days in S̱híráz."],
    "mention_idxs": [363, 364]
  },
  {
    "canonical_name": "Siyyid Ḥusayn-i-Azg̱handí",
    "entity_type": "person",
    "side": "",
    "is_new": true,
    "db_statements": ["he was warmly welcomed by his maternal uncle, Siyyid Ḥusayn-i-Azg̱handí, the foremost mujtahid of that city.", "the mujtahid called upon Mírzá Aḥmad to combat by every means in his power Ḥájí Mírzá Ḵhán’s pernicious influence."],
    "mention_idxs": [374, 375, 376, 377, 378, 380, 381, 382]
  },
  {
    "canonical_name": "Mírzá Taqí, mujtahid of Yazd",
    "entity_type": "person",
    "side": "",
    "is_new": true,
    "db_statements": ["a certain Mírzá Taqí, a man who was wicked, ambitious, and haughty, who had recently returned from Najaf, where he had completed his studies and had been elevated to the rank of mujtahid.", "'after having satisfied myself as to the mischievous character of that compilation, I decided to destroy it. Last night I threw it into the pond.'"],
    "mention_idxs": [376, 377]
  },
  {
    "canonical_name": "Mullá Yúsuf-i-Ardibílí",
    "entity_type": "person",
    "side": "Bábí",
    "is_new": true,
    "db_statements": ["Mullá Yúsuf-i-Ardibílí, likewise, was subjected in those days to a persecution fiercer and more determined than the savage onslaught which the people of Yazd had directed against Mullá Ṣádiq."],
    "mention_idxs": [382, 383]
  },
  {
    "canonical_name": "Mírzá ‘Abdu’lláh-i-G̱hawg̱há",
    "entity_type": "person",
    "side": "",
    "is_new": true,
    "db_statements": ["The incident was related to me by a certain Mírzá ‘Abdu’lláh-i-G̱hawg̱há, who, while in Kirmán, had heard it from the lips of Ḥájí Siyyid Javád himself."],
    "mention_idxs": [369]
  },
  {
